s</h2>
<div class=3D"textBlock"><p>Here we will explain how to calculate the proba=
bility of multiple events. With 3 events, we have various choices:</p>
<ul>
<li>Calculate the probability of all 3 events occurring;</li>
<li>Calculate the probability of at least one occurring;</li>
<li>Calculate the probability of exactly one occurring;</li>
<li>Calculate the probability of at least two occurring;</li>
<li>Calculate the probability of exactly two occurring; and</li>
<li>Calculate the probability of none of them occurring.</li>
</ul>
<p>The formulas for the probability of 3 events are closely related to the =
formulas we've seen for two events. Introducing the event <span class=3D"ma=
